CHOLERA - VENEZUELA (18)
************************
A ProMED-mail post
[see
Cholera, New Control Measures - Caracas 970802095038
Cholera, new control measures - Venezuela (Caracas... 970902112707
Cholera - Venezuela (17) 970926004450
and 18 other postings]
Date: Thu, 25 Sep 1997 10:48:46 -0700
From: Dave Coder <dcoder@u.washington.edu>
Source: Caracas newspaper, 25 September, 1997

After a respite of three days, four new cases of cholera were reported in the
neighborhood of Las Malvinas de El Valle. Since the recent outbreak began in
June, there have been 188 cases of cholera registered (75 in the La Planta
jail), and three deaths in the region.
In the State of Miranda, Irene Engelke, Director of Epidemiology, reported
yesterday two more cases in the prison of El Rodeo, which has reported
nine cases. Thus far, the area of Miranda has reported 48 cases, the
latest have been among inhabitants of the neighborhood of Los Gochos en
Caucaguita. These figures make a total of 236 cases in the capital.
